Description: RECR_BPP1 - Experimental evidence at protein level: Swiss-Prot protein existence level 1. Catalyzes site-specific recombination between two 34-base- pair LOXP sites. Its role is to maintain the phage genome as a monomeric unit-copy plasmid in the lysogenic state. From Escherichia phage P1 (Bacteriophage P1).
β-lactamase; bla; confers resistance to ampicillin, carbenicillin, and related antibiotics
transcription terminator for bacteriophage T7 RNA polymerase
bidirectional E. coli tonB-P14 transcription terminator
LacZα fragment of β-galactosidase; lacZ fragment
